sms_tool
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Derived from: obsy/sms_tool  <https://github.com/obsy/sms_tool>
License:      Apache License, Version 2.0
              <https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0>

The bundled `dependencies/sms_tool` is a MODIFIED build of the above work. The
modifications (see `dependencies/sms_tool.patch`, applied to `sms_main.c`) are:

  1. Change the default AT device from `/dev/ttyUSB0` to `/dev/smd11`.
  2. Skip termios setup (`tcgetattr`/`tcsetattr`) on non-TTY character devices
     via an `isatty()` guard in `setserial()`.
  3. Apply the same `isatty()` guard to the exit-time termios restore in
     `resetserial()`.
  4. Exit cleanly (`exit(1)`) on port open/reopen/fdopen failure instead of
     dereferencing an invalid stream and crashing; gate verbose open traces
     behind the existing `-D` debug flag.

No other changes were made. A copy of the Apache License 2.0 is available at the
URL above. This binary is redistributed under the terms of that license.
